<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-272-034  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 272 034.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  May 15 1989 v8 n10 p85(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>GSA develops security course. (General Services Administration)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Power, Kevin.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Statute:   Computer Security Act of 1987 (interpretation and construction).andO;Topic:     United States. General Services AdministrationSecurityTrainingComputer SystemsAccess Controls.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GSA Develops Security CourseandM;The General Services Administration has developed a computer securityawareness course to help agencies meet the Computer Security Act's basictraining requirement.andM;The new course was designed by GSA's Property, Supply and Security ManagementTraining Institute and covers threats to computer systems, computer securitypractices and national computer security policies and procedures.andP;  GSA hasused the 3-1/2-hour course to train its employees.andP;  Officials recentlydecided to make it available to other agencies and state and localgovernments.andM;Roger Melton, director of GSA's training center, said the course is ascaled-down version of a GSA course for systems security officers.andP;  He saidGSA tracked the progress of the Computer Security Act in an effort to preparefor any new training requirements.andM;&quot;What we did was follow the act,&quot; Melton said.andP;  &quot;We had developed a five-daycourse, but we said let's make sure we have a course briefing that meets thebasic requirements and intent of the law.andP;  We tried to stay ahead of thegame.&quot;andP;  A recent General Accounting Office report said some agencies have notbegun security awareness training, but Melton said the course can satisfytraining needs quickly.andM;The course costs $130 per person or $2,600 for groups of up to 100.andP;  GSA hasscheduled 11 training sessions to be held in Washington beginning this month.andO;Another 13 sessions will be held from April 10 through Sept. 1 in New York,Boston, Philadelphia, Atlanta, Denver, Salt Lake City, San Francisco, andFort worth and San Antonio, Texas.andM;For information about the course contact GSA's Training Center, tel.andO;703-557-0986.andO;</TEXT></DOC>